## Capsule Brain configuration template
## ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
## Copy this file to `.env` and adjust the values to match your environment.
## `scripts/run_dev.sh` relies on the exact variable names listed here when it
## exports the configuration prior to launching the development stack, so keep
## the keys even if you override the defaults. Avoid checking a populated
## `.env` into source control.

## =============================================================================
## API server (FastAPI served by uvicorn)
## =============================================================================
## `CB_API_HOST` feeds the Kubernetes and Docker compose manifests located under
## `deploy/` as well as `scripts/run_dev.sh`. The dev launcher binds to
## `0.0.0.0` regardless, but customizing the default keeps the generated `.env`
## aligned with your target topology. `CB_API_PORT` is read both by uvicorn and
## by the dev script when it builds the API URL.
CB_API_HOST=0.0.0.0
CB_API_PORT=8000

## =============================================================================
## Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS)
## =============================================================================
## Provide a comma-separated list of allowed browser origins. Do not include
## spaces between entries so FastAPI parses the values correctly. Include both
## `localhost` and `127.0.0.1` variants during local development to avoid
## confusing preflight failures when browsers mix DNS and loopback addresses.
ALLOW_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000,http://localhost:8000,http://127.0.0.1:8000

## =============================================================================
## Authentication secrets for admin interfaces (Capsule Brain + overseer)
## =============================================================================
## These values gate administrative access for both the FastAPI admin surface
## and the overseer service in `teacher/`. Generate new secrets before deploying
## anywhere other than your local machine and rotate them regularly in
## production scripts.
ADMIN_TOKEN=your_admin_token_here
ADMIN_API_KEY=your_admin_api_key_here

## =============================================================================
## Large language model (LLM) provider API keys
## =============================================================================
## Set at least one provider. Leave unused providers commented out so the dev
## script does not export empty values into your shell. When using Azure OpenAI
## you must configure the Azure deployment-specific variables separately in
## `deploy/` manifests or your hosting platform.
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_key_here
# COHERE_API_KEY=your_cohere_key_here
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your_azure_openai_api_key_here

## =============================================================================
## Telemetry and monitoring exporters
## =============================================================================
## Capsule Brain emits OpenTelemetry spans and metrics by default. Flip the flag
## below to `false` if you prefer to disable telemetry locally. The value is
## consumed by both the FastAPI app and `scripts/run_dev.sh`, which forwards it
## to the background services it launches.
TELEMETRY_ENABLE=true

## =============================================================================
## Testing helpers
## =============================================================================
## Integration tests and smoke scripts use this base URL when targeting the API.
## Adjust the scheme, host, or port if your deployment differs from the FastAPI
## defaults above so automated checks point at the correct server.
CB_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000

## =============================================================================
## Legacy launcher / CLI compatibility
## =============================================================================
## The legacy Python entry points (`launch_capsule_brain.py` and
## `run_overseer.py`) still read the generic `HOST` and `PORT` variables
## directly. Keep these synchronized with the `CB_API_*` values until the CLI is
## fully migrated.
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=8000

## =============================================================================
## TLS reverse proxy guidance
## =============================================================================
## Uncomment this when running Capsule Brain behind a TLS-enabled reverse proxy
## (for example, the docker-compose stack in `docker-compose.reverse-proxy.yml`)
## and set it to the externally visible domain name so cookies and redirects use
## the correct host.
# CB_DOMAIN=cb.example.com
